I come here all the time, so I've developed a good feeling for their serving quantities. I can specifically speak to the pancakes.  Really good, and really big (maybe 9" diameter?).  What I'm saying is that if you get the normal size stack of 3, that's like eating a small cake all by yourself ... quite a challenge!  The time before last I ordered a short stack of 2, and even that was a challenge.  This time, I asked for a single one ($2.99) with chocolate and bananas mixed in.  That's not specifically listed, but they do it no problem.  Excellent, and just the right amount!!

Bella greeted us warmly and we were seated immediately.  The atmosphere was diverse and friendly. The coconut french toast was delish with real butter and plenty of coconut. The maple syrup dispenser on the table was full to the brim ( and clean!)The Cornedbeef Reuben on marble rye was chuck full of piping hot,tasty, not too salty, beef with melt in your mouth sourcrout and swiss.  Bella assured me  my side of slaw was fresh. It was an overflowing side dish of crunchy, crispy, just a hint of sweetness, heaven. Half dill was flavorful and sliced heartily. Bella came back multiple times to refill our coffee cups & creamers and check on our progress. Too stuffed for dessert but baklava looked tempting...next time. Highly recommend this spot in a city full of processed, cheap imitators. Village and it's people are the real deal!

Nice setup, not too big, not too small. Plenty of wait staff on a Saturday to keep things moving. Definitely looks popular with the locals @11:30 AM.

Best place on the north side of Newton for breakfast or lunch! Friendly staff and terrific food. Try the homemade potato chips of french fries! I love the chicken lemon rice soup. Homemade Greek salad dressing is awesome too!

The wait staff are kind and professional. The food is excellent and the ambiance is halfway between a diner and a restaurant, which is probably why they call it the Village CAFE! At any rate, prices are really reasonable for the food you get! Enjoy! (And I'm not even getting a kickback!)
The food is really good. I'd recommend the tuna melt or buffalo chicken salad, and the breakfast food is great. Also it's really cheap.

This is a great restaurant with homemade foods and fresh fruit.  The breakfast hash is superb.  Very friendly staff.  Comfortable atmosphere.  I meet clients and conduct business here with plenty of space and good food.
Hidden gem!
I love Village Cafe!  Good food, no frills, perfect place to grab breakfast of lunch with a friend.  The owner is a super nice guy who clearly cares about his business.
